########################################################################################################################
# CEDAR INSTALLATION

Compact installation instructions:

1. Take a look at the configuration file 'cedar.conf' and see if you would like to make any changes
   (e.g., installation prefix).
2. Create an out-of-source build folder and change into it:
   $ mkdir build
   $ cd build 
3. Call cmake to generate UNIX makefiles:
   $ cmake ..
4. Compile cedar:
   $ make all # you can append '-j n' to split the compilation process into n threads
[Optional: Run all unit tests:
   $ make test
]
5a. For all Debian based Linux distributions: Create installation package and install it:
   $ make package
   $ sudo dpkg -i cedar-<version>-Linux.deb
5b. Manual installation:
   $ make install
   
